# 12. Security Considerations

This module follows:

* 005 - Security Standards

The following security requirements are specific to the Roles & Permissions module.

---

## Authorization

Every protected backend request must evaluate authorization before executing business logic.

Authorization must never be performed on the frontend.

---

## Permission Evaluation

Permissions are evaluated using the authenticated user's assigned roles.

Permissions are never evaluated using user-specific permission assignments.

---

## Least Privilege

Users should receive only the permissions required to perform their responsibilities.

Avoid granting excessive permissions.

---

## System Roles

System roles:

* Cannot be deleted.
* Cannot be renamed.
* Cannot be deactivated.
* Cannot lose mandatory permissions.

Only custom roles are editable.

---

## Permission Integrity

Permission definitions are owned by the system.

Firms cannot create new permission codes.

Firms may only assign existing permissions to custom roles.

---

## Cross-Firm Isolation

Users may only manage:

* Roles
* Role assignments
* Permission assignments

within their own firm.

Cross-firm authorization is prohibited.

---

## Role Assignment

Only authorized users may assign or remove roles.

Every role assignment must be validated before persistence.

---

## Authorization Middleware

Every protected API endpoint must use centralized authorization middleware.

Business modules must never duplicate permission evaluation logic.

---

# 13. Acceptance Criteria

The module is complete only if all of the following are true.

---

## Role Management

* System roles exist.
* Custom roles can be created.
* Custom roles can be updated.
* Custom roles can be deleted.
* System roles cannot be deleted.

---

## Permission Management

* All system permissions exist.
* Permissions can be assigned to roles.
* Duplicate assignments are prevented.

---

## User Role Assignment

* Users may have multiple roles.
* Roles may be assigned.
* Roles may be removed.
* Effective permissions update immediately.

---

## Authorization

* Authorized requests succeed.
* Unauthorized requests return HTTP 403.
* Permission evaluation is consistent across every module.

---

## Testing

* Unit tests pass.
* Integration tests pass.
* Authorization middleware is tested.
* Permission evaluation is tested.

